"title": "2505: Jesus Christ, ascension of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "2505: jesus christ, ascension of",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The return of Jesus Christ to his Father in order to establish his kingdom, having completed his work on earth.</p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ's ascension described</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:9-Acts1:11\">ACT 1:9–1:11</a></strong> <em>As in the OT, the cloud symbolises God's presence.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark16:19\">MRK 16:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:51\">LUK 24:51</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:2\">ACT 1:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:10\">EPH 4:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim3:16\">1TI 3:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:24\">HEB 9:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:22\">1PE 3:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev12:5\">REV 12:5</a></p>\n<h2>Predictions of Jesus Christ's ascension</h2>\n<h3>In the OT</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:7-Eph4:8\">EPH 4:7–4:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps68:18\">PSA 68:18</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ looks forward to his ascension as his return to his Father</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John16:28\">JHN 16:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:62\">JHN 6:62</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John7:33\">JHN 7:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:28\">JHN 14:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John16:5\">JHN 16:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John16:10\">JHN 16:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:11\">JHN 17:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:13\">JHN 17:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:17\">JHN 20:17</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ establishes his kingdom by his ascension</h2>\n<h3>He ascended to send the Holy Spirit</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John16:7\">JHN 16:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John7:39\">JHN 7:39</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:16-John14:19\">JHN 14:16–14:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:25-John14:26\">JHN 14:25–14:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:26-John15:27\">JHN 15:26–15:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:33\">ACT 2:33</a></p>\n<h3>He ascended to prepare a place for his people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:2-John14:4\">JHN 14:2–14:4</a></strong></p>\n<h3>He ascended to exaltation and glory</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:26\">LUK 24:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:33\">ACT 2:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:20-Eph1:21\">EPH 1:20–1:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:22\">1PE 3:22</a></p>\n<h3>He ascended to exercise his high priestly ministry</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb4:14\">HEB 4:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb7:25\">HEB 7:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:24\">HEB 9:24</a></p>\n<h3>He ascended so that believers may follow him</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess4:17\">1TH 4:17</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ's ascension indicates the manner of his return</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:11\">ACT 1:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:30\">MAT 24:30</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:26\">MRK 13:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke21:27\">LUK 21:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:7\">REV 1:7</a></p>",
